OL,3,CChoosing a new pope: How the Vatican
OL,4,Cturns it's smoke signals black or white
OL,6,FFor those outside the chapel, the only
OL,7,Fsign comes from the smoke produced by
OL,8,Fburning the ballots on the chapel's
OL,9,Froof after each round of voting.
OL,11,FThe colour of the smoke tells the
OL,12,Fstory: black means no cardinal has
OL,13,Fsecured the required two-thirds
OL,14,Fmajority, while white signals that the
OL,15,Fcardinals have reached a consensus and
OL,16,Felected a new pope.
