OL,3,CChoosing a new pope: How the Vatican
OL,4,Cturns it's smoke signals black or white
OL,6,FThe tradition of using smoke dates
OL,7,Fback to the 1800s, but the first
OL,8,Frecorded use of white and black smoke
OL,9,Fto mark the result was at the 1903
OL,10,FConclave.
OL,12,FHow is the smoke created?
OL,14,FInside the Sistine Chapel, two stoves
OL,15,Fare temporarily set up for the
OL,16,Fconclave, both connected to a flue - a
OL,17,Fpipe within a chimney - that leads the
OL,18,Fsmoke up through the chapel roof and
OL,19,Foutside.
