OL,3,CChoosing a new pope: How the Vatican
OL,4,Cturns it's smoke signals black or white
OL,6,FAfter each voting session, chemicals
OL,7,Fare burned in the right stove to
OL,8,Fproduce either a black or white colour
OL,9,Ffor the smoke that is created in the
OL,10,Fleft stove, where the ballots are
OL,11,Fburned.
OL,13,FFor black smoke, a chemical compound
OL,14,Fof potassium perchlorate, anthracene,
OL,15,Fand sulfur is used to make the smoke
OL,16,Fdarker.
OL,18,FTo create the white smoke, a mixture
OL,19,Fof potassium chloride, lactose, and
OL,20,Famber conifer resin is added to make
OL,21,Fit more visible.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/6
